    align:rationale "Both concepts clearly refer to data used for AI system validation. However, the AIDOC definition is more specific, detailing *how* that data is used (model evaluation, tuning parameters, preventing overfitting/underfitting). dpv-ai provides a broader, more general description of 'data involved in validation'. This difference prevents an exact match but indicates strong similarity suitable for interchangeability in many contexts."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:DataValidation ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/dpv/ai#ValidationData> .

