    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts address the process of improving data quality by addressing errors and inconsistencies. While 'Data Wrangling/Cleaning' (AIDOC) encompasses enrichment as well, and 'DataCleaning' (dpv-ai) focuses specifically on cleaning, the core activity is highly overlapping. The lexical similarity score of 0.689 supports a close, but not exact, match."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:DataWrangling ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/dpv/ai#DataCleaning> .

align:3568a781-6cad-4dca-b227-b58a039b866f a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:402bfd97-c4c2-4676-bf34-dbb149e6db7d ;
    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts relate to the infrastructure and process for machine learning. 'MachineLearningPlatform' (dpv-ai) focuses on the *technology* enabling ML, while 'Machine Learning Pipeline' (AIDOC) emphasizes the *activities* within that platform. They are highly related and often co-occur, but aren’t strictly interchangeable; a pipeline is *run on* a platform. The lexical similarity score of 0.604 supports this close relationship."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:MLPipeline ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/dpv/ai#MachineLearningPlatform> .

