    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts refer to the capabilities of AI systems. The AIDOC concept focuses on *what* an AI system can do (sensory, knowledge, control), while dpv-ai provides a more comprehensive definition encompassing purpose, autonomy and outputs. They are highly related but not interchangeable due to differing levels of detail and focus; thus, closeMatch is appropriate."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:AISystemCapability ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/dpv/ai#AISystem> .

